         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">10/9/82. ¶  ¶ My best thanks are due to you, honored and venerable Sir, that you so obligingly inquired into the claims of Vahea. I hope, that I have not been indiscrete in giving publicity to that po...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.09.10b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">10/9/82.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My best thanks are due to you, honored and venerable Sir, that you so obligingly inquired into the claims of <name key="Vahea">Vahea</name>. I hope, that I have not been indiscrete in giving publicity to that portion of your last kind letter. I had just to write an article (gratis) for the monthly number of the pharmaceutic Society of Victoria, as a honor. Member, and was glad of the opportunity, to seize on a subject interesting for pharmaceutic readers.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B82.09.01. See A. de Candolle to M, 27 July 1882 (in this edition as 82-07-27a), quoted extensively in M's article.</p>
               </note> With all others I admire your working power at so advanced an age! You must feel happy, to have maintained the high name of your illustrious father so well and so long, and that a gifted and assiduous son follows your footsteps.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At the end of the year I shall be able to send you the "census" of the Austral. plant-<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">species</hi>
               </seg>, which is now printed as far as <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name> (<name key="Stylideae">Stylideae</name>) as a Commentary to the Flor. Australiensis and the fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.03.04.</p>
               </note> I have restored Labillardières first <name key="Candollea">Candollea</name> and also Loureiro's <name key="Stylidium">Stylidium</name>. I hope the change will be pleasing to you and M. Casimir de Candolle, as it is now a grand monument in bot. science dedicatory.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Eucalyptography is in arrear, because the Gov. Printing office is partly burnt down.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am greatly beholden to you for sending me so kindly your essay on Darwin.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. de Candolle (1882a).</p>
               </note> I greatly admire his "voyage",<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Darwin (1839).</p>
               </note> his geologic researches, but not his "adscende" theories.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Darwin (1859).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful and grateful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I feel greatly obliged to Dr Fournier also.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>De Candolle, in the extract of his letter published by M, reported having had help from Fournier in Paris in answering M's query.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Like with <name key="Hevea">Hevea</name>, <name key="Centipeda">Centipeda</name>, <name key="Floriscopa">Floriscopa</name> &amp;c Botanists will become quickly accustomed to use the name <name key="Candollea">Candollea</name> instead of <name key="Stylidium">Stylidium</name>.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
